data.description: Built in 1895 by the famed Perkins Lumber Mill, this classic four-square Victorian home sits on a wonderful lot in a highly desirable neighborhood in historic downtown. A covered porch stretches across the front of the home and overlooks the gardens with iron fencing, stone paths and a patio. A vintage oak front door opens into a foyer featuring the original staircase and newel post. Double doors in the foyer open into a spacious living room with a gas-log fireplace and heart pine floors. The adjoining dining room has a built-in cabinet and French doors that open into a private office. The kitchen is spacious with granite counters and a copper sink. A powder room completes the main level. The upstairs has three bedrooms, a full bath with a vintage cabinet vanity, walk-in shower and a laundry room. Fresh exterior paint and a new architectural shingle roof in June 2023. There are three off-street parking spaces and a detached garage that could be a workshop. Walk to the best restaurants and shops in Eureka Springs!
